{"id": 1971, "source": "pestle", "subject": "physics", "course": null, "level": "HL", "paper": "1", "year": "2021", "session": "21M", "subtopic": "12-1-the-interaction-of-matter-with-radiation", "title": "21M.1.HL.TZ2.40", "topic_id": "12", "source_url": "https://pestle.pages.dev/app/", "question_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p>An electron of non-relativistic speed <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi></math> interacts with an atom. All the energy of the electron is transferred to an emitted photon of frequency <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math> . An electron of speed <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>v</mi></math> now interacts with the same atom and all its energy is transmitted to a second photon. What is the frequency of the second photon?</p>\n<p>A.  <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>f</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>B.  <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>f</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>C.  <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>f</mi></math></p>\n<p>D.  <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mi>f</mi></math></p>\n</div>", "solution_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p>D</p>\n</div>", "examiners_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n[N/A]\n</div>"}